import React from 'react'; function Projects() { return (

Projects

Data and Machine Learning

COVID-19 Data Analysis Using SQL and Tableau

This project involves analyzing global COVID-19 datasets with advanced SQL techniques, including joins, CTEs, and window functions to uncover trends and patterns. The analysis is complemented by an interactive Tableau dashboard that visualizes key insights, such as case trends, mortality rates, and geographical impact. This project highlights proficiency in SQL for complex data manipulation and the use of Tableau for data visualization. View the project on GitHub.

Data Cleaning and Correlation Analysis in Python

This project focused on cleaning and transforming raw housing datasets for enhanced analysis, leveraging Python's powerful libraries like Pandas, NumPy, and Matplotlib. View the project details on GitHub.

Stock Market Price Prediction Using LSTM

This project involves developing a machine learning model using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks to forecast stock prices for major companies. Explore the project on GitHub.

Real-Time Stock Market Data Pipeline with Apache Kafka and AWS

Designed and implemented a real-time stock market data pipeline utilizing Apache Kafka on AWS EC2 for seamless data ingestion and processing. See the project in action on GitHub.



NSF & Cloud and DevOps

Indoor Navigation System for Assistive Technology

Contributed to an NSF-funded research project focusing on building an indoor navigation system to assist visually impaired and wheelchair users. Read more about the project on GitHub.

Netflix Clone Deployment Using Kubernetes

A Netflix Clone was deployed on Kubernetes, utilizing AWS EC2 for hosting, Jenkins for CI/CD pipelines, and Prometheus and Grafana for monitoring. Learn more about this project on GitHub.

); } export default Projects;
